## ğŸ“Š Common Scenarios

### Dashboard Card
```svelte
<div class="bg-card border border-card-border rounded-lg p-6 shadow-md">
  <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground mb-2">Revenue</h3>
  <div class="text-3xl font-semibold">$12,345</div>
  <p class="text-sm text-success mt-2">+12.5% from last month</p>
</div>
```

### Form Field
```svelte
<div class="space-y-2">
  <label class="text-sm font-medium">Email</label>
  <input 
    type="email"
    class="w-full px-3 py-2 rounded-md border border-input 
           focus:border-input-focus focus:ring-2 focus:ring-ring 
           transition-colors"
  />
  <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">We'll never share your email.</p>
</div>
```

### Status Indicator
```svelte
<div class="flex items-center gap-2">
  <div class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-success"></div>
  <span class="text-sm">Active</span>
</div>
```

### Chart Integration
```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import { semantic } from '$shared/styles/tokens';
  import { Line } from 'svelte-chartjs';
  
  const data = {
    datasets: [{
      label: 'Revenue',
      borderColor: semantic.primary.DEFAULT,
      backgroundColor: semantic.chart[1],
    }]
  };
</script>

<Line {data} />
```

---

## ğŸ¯ Key Takeaways

1. **Tailwind first**: 99% of UI uses Tailwind classes
2. **Semantic tokens**: Never hardcode colors
3. **Interactive states**: Always add hover/active/focus
4. **Contrast**: Use `text-*-foreground` pairing
5. **Transitions**: Smooth UX with `transition-colors`
6. **Type safety**: Use ButtonVariant, StatusVariant
7. **TypeScript tokens**: Only for Canvas/Charts/programmatic logic
8. **Dark theme**: Automatic via `prefers-color-scheme` (cards, muted, borders adapt)

